[3] Diarrhea - Honduras
Date: Tue 23 Nov 2010
Source: La Tribuna (in Spanish trans. Corr.SB) [edited]
<http://www.latribuna.hn/web2.0/?p=210866>


Cases of diarrhea in children under 15 have increased by 279 cases
during epidemiological week number 45 [7-13 Nov 2010], with higher
incidence in Choloma, Puerto Cortes, Villanueva, and Omoa.

Delia Tercero, the Regional Department of Health epidemiologist,
reported that 87 patients were older than 15 years old, so that (the
department) began an investigation, to determine what accounted for
this increase. "Most cases are in minors, and are allegedly caused by
bad food handling or improper storage of the same. Housewives, or
those who prepare food, are urged to keep a strict control of hygiene
when cooking."

Tercero indicated that if the percentage of cases in adults increases
investigations will be undertaken to confirm if the diarrhea is due
to poisoning through contaminated food or the water supply.

--
